3-11T08:19:32.000Z","metadata":{"markets":["All"],"_id":"661d30b6252ffca245926b7b"},"search":["Connecting Rod Big End Journal Checking, Measuring and Bearing Selection","Wipe clean the V-blocks and crankshaft main bearing journals.","Position the crankshaft on a set of V-blocks.","V-blocks","Crankshaft","Failure to calibrate a micrometer may lead to an incorrect clearance being obtained.","Severe engine damage could result from incorrect clearance resulting in loss of motorcycle control and an accident.","The crankshaft journals diameters can be measured using a suitable micrometer.","Due to the techniques used during manufacture, the crankshaft cannot be reground and oversize bearings are not available.","If any journal has worn beyond the service limit, the crankshaft must be replaced.","Wipe clean the crankshaft big end bearing journals.","Calibrate the micrometer.","Always use a micrometer that can record readings accurate to 0.001 mm","Measure the big end bearing in three positions and record the results. (see Big End Bearing Selection)","Stage 1 - Position the micrometer (1) on the crankshaft away from the oil feed hole and record the measurement.","Stage 2 - Rotate the micrometer120 degrees (2) around the crankshaft and record the measurement.","Stage 3 - Rotate the micrometer a further 120 degrees (3) around the crankshaft and record the measurement.","Measurement 1 (0 degrees)","Measurement 2 (+120 degrees from zero point)","Measurement 3 (+240 degrees from zero point )","For the crankshaft's specifications refer to ","Crankshaft",".","Connecting Rod Bearing Selection","Minor differences in dimensions are compensated for by using selective bearings.","For further information on bearing part number to colour cross-references, refer to the EPC.","Note the big end bore grade (see Big End Bearing Selection).","Record each of the crankshaft's big end journal diameters (see Big End Bearing Selection).","Using the Big End Bearing Selection Chart, cross reference the journals diameter with the big end bore grade and select the correct size bearings.","It is normal for the bearings selected to differ from one journal to another.","It is also normal for there to be two options of bearing shell colour. In such cases, pick the shell size that gives the greater running clearance.","Repeat the measurements for the remaining big end bearings.","Connecting rod","Connecting rod big end cap","Big end bore (grade 1 or 2)","Fit the new bearings.","Rocol Dry Molybdenum Disulphide lubricant is a high content molybdenum disulphide soft paste which is designed to lubricate mechanisms where a wet lubricant cannot be tolerated.","Lubricate the threads and the face of the fixing with Rocol Dry Molybdenum Disulphide paste. ","Connecting Rod Big End Bearing Selection Chart","From engine number AZ7875 new connecting rods, bearing shells and connecting rod bolts were fitted and can be identified by the larger M9 fixings. These connecting rods are not required to be replaced if the connecting rod bolts are loosened or removed.","For engines built up to engine AZ7874 and having M8 connecting rod bolts, the connecting rod, big end cap, bearings and connecting rod bolts must be replaced if the connecting rod bolts are loosened or removed.","Parts Kits","If required the following kits are available containing:","three connecting rods, bearing shells and M8 bolts, refer to the EPC for the part number. The connecting rods in this kit must be replaced if the connecting rods are loosened or removed.","three connecting rods, bearing shells and M9 bolts, refer to the EPC for the part number. The connecting rods in this kit do not need to be replaced if the connecting rod bolts are loosened or removed.","bearing shells and M9 bolts, refer to the EPC for the part number. This kit is only for engines that have the M9 connecting rod bolts fitted.","The spares kit containing the M8 connecting rod bolts must only be fitted to engines up to engine number AZ7874. The connecting rods in this kit must be replaced if the connecting rods are loosened or removed.","For bearing shell selection up to engine number AZ7874 refer to ","Up to engine number AZ7874 or M8 connecting rod bolts"," table below.","The spares kit containing the M9 connecting rod bolts can be fitted to all engines for this model. The connecting rods in this kit do not need to be replaced if the connecting rod bolts are loosened or removed.","For bearing shell selection when fitting the kits containing the M9 bolts refer to ","From engine number AZ7875 or M9 connecting rod bolts"," table below.","Failure to follow the advice above may lead to loss of motorcycle control which could result in serious injury or death.","Bearing Shell Selection Tables","Use the table below to select the correct bearing shell colour.","Up to engine number AZ7874 with M8 connecting rod bolts, refer to the table below for big end bearing shell selection.","Up to engine number AZ7874 or M8 connecting rod bolts","Connecting rod big end bore Diameter","Minimum","42.008","42.008","42.014","42.014","Maximum","42.015","42.015","42.020","42.020","Grade","1","1","2","2","Crankshaft big end journal diameter","Minimum","39.001","38.992","39.001","38.992","Maximum","39.008","39.000","39.008","39.000","Bearing shell cover","Red","White","Blue","For instance:","Measurement","Cylinder One","Cylinder Two","Cylinder Three","Connecting rod big end bore Diameter","42.010","42.014","42.015","Connecting Rod Big End Bore Grade","1","2","1","Measurement - 1 (0 degrees)","39.001 mm","39.004 mm","38.972 mm","Measurement - 2 (+120 degrees)","39.003 mm","39.004 mm","38.973mm","Measurement - 3 (+240 degrees from zero point )","39.002 mm","39.004 mm","38.973mm","Bearing Shell Colour Required ","Red","White","Blue","From engine number AZ7875 and earlier engines fitted with the M9 connecting rod bolts, refer to the table below for big end bearing shell selection.","From engine number AZ7875 or M9 connecting rod bolts"